free_memory_o...ressed_objects(25.10)    free_memory_o...ressed_objects(25.10)

Name
       free_memory_of_compressed_objects - Releases all the excess memory used
       by dbGet

Syntax
        free_memory_of_compressed_objects

       [-help]

       Releases all the excess memory used by dbGet. When the dbGet command is
       used to query sWire or sVia under the compressed PG mode, it causes in-
       creased memory usage. This is because fake objects are created rapidly,
       but  those  cannot  be  released automatically. The free_memory_of_com-
       pressed_objects command is used to release such  fake  objects  and  to
       free such occupied memory for the user. Hence, the command reduces mem-
       ory consumption caused by dbGet in the compressed PG mode.

       Note:  The object pointer released through this command becomes invalid
       and cannot be queried.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each free_memory_of_compressed_objects parame-
              ter. For a detailed description of the command and all its para-
              meters, use the man command:

              man free_memory_of_compressed_objects

Related Information
       dbGet

